1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,639
[The Age of Awakening]

2
00:00:02,639 --> 00:00:05,638
[Episode Twenty-six]

3
00:00:07,520 --> 00:00:09,440
Mom, my brother is eating without permission.

4
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:10,720
Tell him to stop.

5
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:12,080
Wait till dad comes back.

6
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:17,200
Dad's back.

7
00:00:17,360 --> 00:00:18,160
Time to eat, Dad.

8
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,360
Dad, come and eat.

9
00:00:20,480 --> 00:00:21,200
You are back

10
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:22,800
Just in time, wash your hands and eat.

11
00:00:26,080 --> 00:00:26,720
No.

12
00:00:29,887 --> 00:00:31,211
[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhongfu, Dean of Liberal Arts at Peking University]

13
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:33,920
Someone made you angry again?

14
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:34,880
No.

15
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:36,400
Something happened at school?

16
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:37,680
No.

17
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:38,960
Let's eat then.

18
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:39,920
No

19
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:41,760
You don't have to eat, but the kids have to.

20
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:43,520
But the kids won't eat without you starting first

21
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:47,040
If they're hungry, they should just eat.

22
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:49,600
Zimei, Henian.

23
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,040
If you're hungry, eat first.

24
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:52,240
Don't wait for me.

25
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:54,720
Make me look like a feudal parent.

26
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:56,320
Where are you going?

27
00:00:56,560 --> 00:00:57,760
Don't interfere, I am gonna start writing.

28
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:04,480
And you say you're not the feudal parent.

29
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:05,840
I see that you totally are.

30
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:11,520
I'll eat.

31
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,520
Dad, come and eat.

32
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:16,400
Dad, come and eat.

33
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:20,400
Sit down.

34
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,480
Specially made for you, dumplings with chives and eggs filling.

35
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:31,760
Wilson's intervention

36
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:32,880
temporarily hindered

37
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:35,920
Japan pushing its scheme on rights in Shandong Province.

38
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:38,480
But on the second day after

39
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:40,400
Italian Prime Minister Orlando left the Conference,

40
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:43,200
Japan representative Makino Nobuaki

41
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:45,280
seized the chance to talk,

42
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:48,240
insisting the only way to solve the issue on Shandong Province

43
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,000
is to meet his terms.

44
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:53,600
Otherwise, Japan will refuse to sign the peace treaty

45
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:55,520
and quit the Paris Peace Conference.

46
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:58,880
The situation worsens.

47
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:05,680
Beijing Foreign Affairs Committee of the Republic of China

48
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,680
Chairman Wang Daxie.

49
00:02:07,873 --> 00:02:11,108
[Gu Weiju, styled Shaochuan, Ambassador to the United States]

50
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:10,800
America, Britain, France, Italy, and Japan

51
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,400
are holding a second meeting

52
00:02:12,726 --> 00:02:16,515
[Lu Zhengxiang, styled Zixin, Head of the Chinese delegation at the Paris Peace Conference]

53
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,880
discussing the Shandong issue.

54
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:18,480
The request of Chinese representatives to attend the meeting has been rejected.

55
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,560
From last night until now,

56
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:24,240
we requested three times for a meeting with Wilson,

57
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:25,760
Lloyd George, Clemenceau,

58
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:28,160
yet all have been declined.

59
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:30,320
Please inform us of the countermeasure as soon as possible

60
00:02:28,910 --> 00:02:33,297
[Wang Zhengting, styled Rutang, Plenipotentiary of the Southern Government]

61
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:33,840
Minister,

62
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:37,040
shall we rediscuss the content in this message?

63
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:38,320
There's nothing to discuss!

64
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,960
Send it now. Go!

65
00:02:41,207 --> 00:02:41,591
Yes.

66
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:49,360
Gentlemen,

67
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:53,840
we are at the end of our tether now.

68
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,440
There is only one thing we can do now:

69
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:01,600
wait.

70
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,720
Mr. Zixin, calm down first.

71
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:12,400
Take a break.

72
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:15,840
I'm like an ant in a heating wok right now

73
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:19,360
I don't know which way I should march to for my survival.

74
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,480
How on earth can I calm down?

75
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:24,800
I understand.

76
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,720
But you need to be in a good condition now.

77
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,160
If you break down,

78
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:34,320
we will only be stuck even deeper.

79
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:32,800
Response from Beijing.

80
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:33,840
Read.

81
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:37,760
Seek for President Wilson's help at all costs.

82
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:55,680
Fine, no time for dignity now.

83
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:58,320
Let's seperate into five groups.

84
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,400
Go to the four exits of the conference room respectively

85
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:02,400
and the elevator entrance in the basement, squatting.

86
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:04,240
Whoever sees Wilson,

87
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:05,920
whatever you do, stop him

88
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,200
and inform me quickly.

89
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:09,360
Let's do it.

90
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,080
Go now!

91
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,160
My fellow friends.

92
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:25,520
We have to do this.

93
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:39,120
What kind of diplomacy do we have here?

94
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:40,800
Is this even diplomacy when we are blocking the door?

95
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:12,880
President Wilson.

96
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,400
Please help us,

97
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:18,000
no matter what.

98
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:21,200
Mr. Gu,

99
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:23,040
let me be honest with you.

100
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,640
My second proposal

101
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:25,920
was just rejected.

102
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:26,960
President Wilson,

103
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:28,720
your Fourteen Points

104
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,560
have become a household name in China.

105
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:33,120
Hundreds of millions of Chinese people

106
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:35,920
are looking forward more and more

107
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:38,320
that right favors over might.

108
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:40,400
I remain committed to the plan,

109
00:06:39,686 --> 00:06:42,687
[Woodrow Wilson, President of the United States]

110
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:41,840
but what else can I do now

111
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:42,880
but leave?

112
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:45,200
President Wilson, you are capable.

113
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:46,720
We fully believe

114
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,720
and rely on American influence.

115
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:50,800
General Lu,

116
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,680
let me borrow a phrase from Chinese.

117
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:57,440
If I had known this day was going to happen, I wouldn't have lived it.

118
00:06:57,520 --> 00:06:59,360
Had it not been for

119
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:01,040
the Twenty-one Articles that you signed

120
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:02,800
in the willing agreement of Zhang Zongxiang

121
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:03,440
Gentleman,

122
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:04,400
I think we would be

123
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:07,360
in a very different situation right now.

124
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:08,720
Mr. President,

125
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:12,480
is there really no chance that you will fix it?

126
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,800
It all depends on your own effort

127
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,480
tomorrow at the convention.

128
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,880
You are the last hope.

129
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,800
Gentlemen, good day.

130
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:00,080
Don't work too hard, Shaochuan.

131
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:03,760
How's the preparation going?

132
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:08,720
A total mess.

133
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:11,440
Brother Zixin,

134
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:14,720
do you think there is any hope for us?

135
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,640
Hope?

136
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:23,120
Like treating a dead horse as if it's alive.

137
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,920
We will give them our dying kicks.

138
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:28,320
We must try, right?

139
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:31,200
Shaochuan, you have to understand.

140
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,680
This speech of yours

141
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:37,280
is our last hope to save ourselves.

142
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:42,160
Please.

143
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,120
Brother Zixin,

144
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,080
I've never understood why

145
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,480
since the Republic of China,

146
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,640
so many once ambitious people committed suicide.

147
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,640
Shaochuan, I know.

148
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:08,000
I put you on the spot.

149
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:10,400
If it was not for the guilt I have on my back

150
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:12,160
for signing the Twenty-one Demands,

151
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:13,760
I will never let you rush to the front

152
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:16,160
of tomorrow's conference.

153
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:19,360
Here.

154
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,080
You see,

155
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:23,520
I found your favorite stinky tofu.

156
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:31,520
Stinky tofu with bread, a combination of Chinese and Western food.

157
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:37,280
Brother Zixin,

158
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:39,840
thanks for your consideration

159
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:44,480
Don't worry, I won't back down.

160
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:50,560
There's still some time for me to get ready.

161
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,200
Shaochuan,

162
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:11,440
on behalf of hundreds of millions of Chinese,

163
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:15,280
thank you.

164
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,160
This taste is the best.

165
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:57,920
Messenger.

166
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:00,480
Chief.

167
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:04,640
Send the message to Beijing:

168
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:07,760
The proposal of five countries jointly administering Shandong,

169
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,280
put forward by President Wilson

170
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,920
on the conference,

171
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:14,320
was rejected again by Makino Nobuaki.

172
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:19,520
Britain and France have acquiesced in Japan's proposal.

173
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:21,680
America's intervention failed.

174
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:24,320
Tomorrow,

175
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:32,160
we will make a last-ditch effort at the conference.

176
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:18,320
Despite all the efforts and work from the Chinese delegation

177
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:20,240
that Shandong shall be returned to China,

178
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:23,280
the British and French government in 1917

179
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:26,080
supported Japan,

180
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,520
on the grounds of the obligation of signed articles with Japan.

181
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:30,320
The British Prime Minister even said

182
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,560
if Japan does not join the League of Nations,

183
00:12:32,880 --> 00:12:34,800
Britain will follow.

184
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:37,600
With Italy has withdrawn from the peace conference,

185
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:39,600
pushed by his eagerness to establish the League of Nations,

186
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:42,320
U.S. President Wilson,

187
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:46,080
worried that without three countries among the Big Five

188
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,400
and that his scheme wouldn't be accompolished,

189
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:50,720
changed his mind and secretly reached an agreement with Japan,

190
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:52,800
supporting Japan to acquire Shandong.

191
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:53,520
The situation

192
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:54,960
hung by a thread.

193
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:55,920
Smell this, Xingang.

194
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:57,360
The grass grows.

195
00:12:56,762 --> 00:12:59,356
[Peking University]

196
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:59,680
The air smells of spring.

197
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:01,280
Stop it, stop it.

198
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:05,920
I feel a little numb when I smell this.

199
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:07,520
We are in the campus now.

200
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,480
We can't be too intimate.

201
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,160
So what?

202
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,040
Spring is coming.

203
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,080
Spring should be like this.

204
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:13,440
It's not like we are dating behind everyone's back.

205
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:16,320
Now that Yannian left, I do miss him.

206
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:17,920
Mr. Zhongfu now leaves me in charge of

207
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:19,760
the delivery and publication of "New Youth".

208
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,040
It's all on me.

209
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:22,320
I'm making real money now.

210
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:23,440
With deep pockets,

211
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:24,640
I can send money to my family.

212
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:27,440
The bitter days have finally come to an end.

213
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:30,720
Bai Lan, I will graduate in three months.

214
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,640
Mr. Zhongfu wants me to work at "New Youth"

215
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:33,920
after graduation

216
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,040
and become a peer editor,

217
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:35,920
and then

218
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:37,760
he wants to recommend me to stay as a teaching assistant.

219
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,680
We can settle in Beijing in the future.

220
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,040
What about the two of us?

221
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:45,360
Didn't you promise to take me back to Qingdao?

222
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:46,080
Sure.

223
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:47,040
Not only go back to Qingdao,

224
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:48,960
I'll also take you to the Zhanqiao Pier.

225
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:52,000
What is the Zhanqiao Pier like?

226
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,880
The Zhanqiao Pier is a long bridge.

227
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,080
It's built on the sea.

228
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:57,680
It goes more than one hundred meters from the seaside.

229
00:13:58,160 --> 00:13:59,920
When there is heavy rain and high tides,

230
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,440
you mustn't go up there alone.

231
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:02,720
Otherwise, if you being not careful,

232
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:03,920
you will be caught in the waves.

233
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:04,880
For real?

234
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:05,520
Yes.

235
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:07,280
What if I fall in?

236
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:08,960
I cannot swim.

237
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,200
Well, in that case,

238
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,280
I'll stand on the pier and laugh,

239
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:14,400
watching you fluttering in the sea.

240
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:16,080
You're not gonna save me?

241
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,120
Nope.

242
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:18,160
Really?

243
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,120
Really.

244
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:20,320
You have to flutter in the sea

245
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:21,600
to learn how to swim.

246
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,600
You're so mean!

247
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,600
I dare you to not save me.

248
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:26,160
I won't save you.

249
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:26,960
You have come to Qingdao.

250
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,160
You can't stay not swimming.

251
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:28,880
Something big has happened!

252
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:29,760
Something big has happened!

253
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:30,320
What's up?

254
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:32,160
Something bad, really bad!

255
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:32,880
Something big has happened!

256
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:34,560
Jianmin Jianmin, wait a minute.

257
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:35,760
Why are you running?

258
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:37,600
Something's wrong in Paris. Shandong is finished.

259
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:38,240
Go!

260
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,640
Something's wrong. Something's wrong.

261
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:42,720
Xingang!

262
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:43,600
Go, go, go, go!

263
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:46,640
Where's the justice?

264
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:48,320
How can they be this unreasonable?

265
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:50,320
A bunch of promise-breaking bastards!

266
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:53,840
I see.

267
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:58,936
[Cai Yuanpei, styled Jiemin, President of Peking University]

268
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:01,520
I swore.

269
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:03,600
This is outragous!

270
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:06,160
At the Paris Peace Conference yesterday,

271
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:09,760
Wilson finally delivered a speech.

272
00:15:10,079 --> 00:15:12,246
[Li Dazhao, styled Shouchang, Director of Peking University Library]

273
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:12,080
He's saying that China should accept its unfortunate fate as it is,

274
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:14,560
and approved Japan's plan

275
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:17,760
that Shandong will be officially handed over to Japan.

276
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:20,080
China's diplomacy has completely failed.

277
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:21,760
What is going on here?

278
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:23,440
Didn't you say two days ago,

279
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:25,360
there's hope that the five countries will govern Shandong?

