00:15:25,680 --> 00:15:26,880
How can that change in a blink?

281
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:28,320
What's going on?

282
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:29,760
Brother Zhongfu,

283
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:31,360
this is the good man in your words.

284
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:32,400
This is what Wilson did.

285
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:33,440
This is a stinking rascal!

286
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,120
Imperialism is full of hooligans!

287
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:36,320
Now,

288
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:39,200
is not the endgame.

289
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:41,760
Maybe there is still room for manoeuvre.

290
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:43,440
Now we have to do our best

291
00:15:43,760 --> 00:15:44,960
to save something.

292
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:46,480
What Peking University can do

293
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:49,440
is to use all platforms and all means

294
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:51,520
speak out loud what is Peking University's attitude to the outside world

295
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,760
and show society the clear stance of Peking University.

296
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:54,800
We will never flinch!

297
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:56,800
Urge the Chinese government and delegation

298
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:58,480
to take the most effective measures

299
00:15:58,880 --> 00:15:59,920
to fight for a final time.

300
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:03,760
Shouchang, Zhongfu, we can only rely on you now.

301
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:06,560
Hurry to publish a special supplement to comment.

302
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:09,280
We need to act quickly.

303
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:12,560
Good.

304
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:17,600
Good. Good.

305
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:34,640
I'm Cai Yuanpei,

306
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:36,640
get me Wang Daxie.

307
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:35,600
By the way, Dongxiu.

308
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:37,440
I want to take a suit with me.

309
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,120
You have to prepare two sets.

310
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:39,920
Alright.

311
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:41,440
This time,

312
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:43,040
there are many speeches and meetings.

313
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:45,040
Please bring me some more shirts.

314
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:47,440
I heard from Junman,

315
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:49,440
everyone in Peking University is busy these two days.

316
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,560
Is this a good time for you to go out?

317
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:55,760
The country and Peking University will be doing just fine without me.

318
00:18:56,480 --> 00:18:58,240
But my teacher, Mr. Dewey, is coming to China.

319
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:00,320
He can't go anywhere without me.

320
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:03,840
Which matter do you think I should attend to?

321
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:06,640
This Beijing is full of shenanigans.

322
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:08,880
Not as peaceful as the countryside.

323
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,400
You can be have your peace.

324
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:12,000
I asked Junman

325
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:14,160
if she can visit you when she is free.

326
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:19,840
I'm done eating.

327
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,360
I'll help you pack the luggage.

328
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:22,240
Okay.

329
00:19:35,360 --> 00:19:38,000
The failure of the Paris Peace Conference spread all over the world.

330
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:40,240
Chinese overseas all felt indignation in their hearts.

331
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:44,080
A large number of Chinese and overseas students poured into Paris,

332
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:48,080
supporting the delegation, also putting pressure on them.

333
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:50,560
They gathered around the residence of the Chinese delegation in Paris,

334
00:19:50,640 --> 00:19:52,800
demanding the delegation to refuse to sign the peace treaty

335
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:55,200
and claiming to defend Shandong to the death.

336
00:19:55,844 --> 00:19:59,929
[Hôtel Lutetia, Paris]

337
00:19:56,080 --> 00:19:57,120
Down with traitors!

338
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:58,160
Give us back Qingdao!

