349
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:15,120
You pretend to be an ostrich, burying your head in the sand?

350
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:16,400
So you are saying,

351
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:17,600
just open them all?

352
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:18,800
Keep it open.

353
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:21,520
It's open. At least we can get some air?

354
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:23,600
Don't you hear them condemning us?

355
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:25,520
The Chief is here.

356
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:30,240
We have become motherless children.

357
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:35,280
Everyone, I sent a message to Qian Nengxun

358
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:36,480
requesting instructions.

359
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:38,080
He said:

360
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:39,200
He can not

361
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:41,200
make the decision to let me go directly to Xu Shichang.

362
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:43,600
Okay then, I turned to Xu Shichang.

363
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:47,440
Still haven't heard back from him.

364
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:50,960
Brother Zixin, what shall we do?

365
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:54,720
We can't resign and commit suicide altogether.

366
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:58,880
Shaochuan,

367
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:00,800
I really have no idea.

368
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:04,560
I went to Wang Daxie for advice again.

369
00:21:05,120 --> 00:21:06,880
He told me the same thing as yesterday.

370
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:09,520
He asked us to propose a compromise.

371
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:11,040
Go to Wilson,

372
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:11,840
Lloyd George,

373
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:12,640
and Clemenceau.

374
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:15,920
Down with traitors! Give us back Qingdao!

375
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:17,440
Down with traitors!

376
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:19,360
Did you hear that? Did you hear that?

377
00:21:19,760 --> 00:21:21,760
In a blink of an eye, we are traitors.

378
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:25,600
Everyone, how can we even look at ourselves now?

379
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:28,880
Give your opinion.

380
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:37,760
I asked our Guangzhou warlord government,

381
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:40,400
the instruction they gave is eight words:

382
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:43,760
fight to death for every inch of land.

383
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:48,480
Strong words, they are.

384
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:50,240
Every inch of the land.

385
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:53,680
You should ask him though.

386
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:55,920
How should we fight?

387
00:21:57,120 --> 00:22:00,160
Brother Zixin, it's over.

388
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:03,520
I think we can only try Wang Daxie's way.

389
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:05,840
We cannot be the traitor

390
00:22:05,950 --> 00:22:07,440
that sits here and waits for the end.

391
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:09,520
Shaochuan.

392
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:11,360
Wang Daxie made it sounds easy.

393
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:14,320
Compromise. How can we compromise?

394
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:16,400
The middle ground

395
00:22:16,480 --> 00:22:18,000
is extremely difficult to grasp.

396
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:22,320
The word traitor

397
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:26,800
is too heavy.

398
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:30,400
If it goes wrong,

399
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:36,080
we might as well pick up this title

400
00:22:38,320 --> 00:22:39,600
with our own hands.

401
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:56,880
Everyone, as for now,

402
00:22:57,520 --> 00:22:59,200
we can't think about personal reputation anymore.

403
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:00,800
Our country has come to the point of the return.

404
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:02,320
We have to fight with all we have.

405
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,720
I dedicate myself to the interests of the country,

406
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:09,280
in life and death irrespective of personal weal and woe.

407
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:11,280
Exactly!

408
00:23:11,760 --> 00:23:12,480
Good!

409
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:14,480
No space for worry and fear.

410
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:16,000
This is our last duty.

411
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:36,240
Go upstairs now.

412
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:38,960
Let's go over every detail.

413
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:46,320
News! Fourteen equals zero!

414
00:23:44,359 --> 00:23:47,971
[Peking University]

415
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:48,880
Wilson invents a new mathematical formula!

416
00:23:49,120 --> 00:23:50,320
Fourteen equals zero!

417
00:23:50,560 --> 00:23:51,760
Come and see! Come and buy!

418
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:53,120
Fourteen equals zero!

419
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:55,440
Wilson's newly invented mathematical formula!

420
00:23:56,000 --> 00:24:00,240
Shizhi, are you leaving Peking University at this time?

421
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:02,080
Is it alright?

422
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:05,840
People will use this against you.

423
00:24:06,560 --> 00:24:09,120
Sir, I've been thinking about this too.

424
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:10,400
I have to do this.

425
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:12,560
Mr. Dewey's visit to China this time

426
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:13,840
was decided long ago.

427
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:14,880
It has already been arranged.

428
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:16,320
If I don't go,

429
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:17,600
there may be some obstacles.

430
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:19,200
Things won't be so smooth.

431
00:24:21,040 --> 00:24:21,760
Unless,

432
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:23,440
his visit to China is cancelled.

433
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:27,840
Dewey's visit to China is no small matter.

434
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:29,840
However,

435
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:32,560
I have this feeling that something serious will happen to Peking University.

436
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:35,200
Don't worry too much, sir.

437
00:24:35,840 --> 00:24:36,960
It can't be that bad.

438
00:24:37,920 --> 00:24:39,600
As long as we know clearly where we stand,

439
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:40,880
we can't count on one Peking University

440
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:42,160
to shake the whole world.

441
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:43,600
Think about this, Sir.

442
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:46,240
Will Paris Peace Conference take orders from Peking University?

443
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:47,600
No.

444
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,440
All we need to do is to make our attitude clear

445
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:50,880
and try our best.

446
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:53,600
This is about the fate of the country.

447
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:57,040
I'm afraid it's not as simple as you think.

448
00:24:58,160 --> 00:24:58,960
I can tell.

449
00:24:59,280 --> 00:25:00,960
Now your mind is not about Peking University.

450
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:02,720
That's fine, you can go.

451
00:25:03,360 --> 00:25:04,480
Sir.

452
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:07,600
Mr. Shizhi.

453
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:11,360
I hope you come back as soon as possible.

454
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:14,400
If something really happens,

455
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:17,040
I will go and get you back.

456
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:19,200
I don't have many helpers around me.

457
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:23,680
After you leave, it's only Zhongfu and Shouchang.

458
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:25,520
You three leaders of new culture,

459
00:25:25,760 --> 00:25:26,880
with one missing.

460
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:29,760
It won't be as powerful without you.

461
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:32,800
Sir, do you know what worries me the most?

462
00:25:33,360 --> 00:25:34,320
Speaking of Zhongfu,

463
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:35,840
what worries me most is him.

464
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:37,440
You know him.

465
00:25:37,680 --> 00:25:40,160
He is over confident and sometimes grumpy.

466
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:42,000
He tends to go too far when things are tricky.

467
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:43,840
It might lead to serious problems.

468
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:45,840
So I invited him

469
00:25:46,320 --> 00:25:47,760
to come with me to Shanghai.

470
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:49,280
But he refused.

471
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:55,600
Mr. Shizhi, you are too young.

472
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,520
You don't know Zhongfu well enough.

473
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:01,840
He must be with Shouchang at this moment.

474
00:26:02,320 --> 00:26:03,440
Shizhi.

475
00:26:06,080 --> 00:26:06,880
Sir.

476
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:08,560
Go and come back soon.

477
00:26:09,120 --> 00:26:11,200
Don't worry, I will, Sir.

478
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:46,400
Down with traitors! Give us back Qingdao!

479
00:26:44,993 --> 00:26:51,209
[Hôtel Lutetia, Paris]

480
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:47,200
Rutang.

481
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:49,120
Give me that file you have.

482
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:49,520
Ok.

483
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:50,640
Here.

484
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:53,040
I've always felt that this wording here can be changed.

485
00:26:53,360 --> 00:26:54,400
It's better to go with this.

486
00:26:57,040 --> 00:26:58,080
Indeed.

487
00:26:58,240 --> 00:26:58,720
It is.

488
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,280
Do what Shaochuan said.

489
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:01,920
All right.

490
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:11,440
Down with traitors! Give us back Shandong!

491
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:14,720
Give us back Qingdao! Give us back Qingdao!

492
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:18,960
Let's eat first, everyone.

493
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:23,040
The hotel was blocked by protesters.

494
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:24,880
Can't go shopping now.

495
00:27:25,360 --> 00:27:26,720
Let's make do with it.

496
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:27,920
Yue.

497
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:29,200
Later.

498
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:31,360
You have to ask those petitioners at the door to leave.

499
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:32,640
Otherwise, we can't get out.

500
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:34,000
That'd be impossible.

501
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:34,960
Just today,

502
00:27:35,040 --> 00:27:36,640
I met with sixteen groups of Chinese representatives.

503
00:27:37,600 --> 00:27:38,880
Those people around the hotel now?

504
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:40,080
It will only be more of them coming.

505
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:42,640
What shall we do then?

506
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:45,600
I asked the hotel for a car.

507
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:47,440
Only three people can get in except the driver.

508
00:27:47,840 --> 00:27:50,240
It's parked in a garage facing the street in the backyard.

509
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:51,760
Quiet area.

510
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:53,360
Few people there, it's safe.

511
00:27:54,320 --> 00:27:55,040
So be it.

512
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:57,040
Shaochuan. Shaochuan.

513
00:27:57,760 --> 00:27:59,120
I can't live without your stinky tofu now.

514
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:08,080
Chief Lu.

515
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,320
Everyone.

516
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:18,400
Everyone. Everyone.

517
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:22,160
The Chinese delegation's compromise plan to U.S. President Wilson,

518
00:28:22,560 --> 00:28:23,040
U.K. Prime Minister

519
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:23,920
Lloyd George,

520
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:26,640
and French Prime Minister Clemenceau

521
00:28:26,720 --> 00:28:27,600
has been printed.

522
00:28:28,080 --> 00:28:29,120
Come, take a look.

523
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:38,320
We did this with the name of traitor on our heads.

524
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:41,200
Four compromise schemes, every detail checked and discussed.

525
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:43,600
If there is no second opinion,

526
00:28:44,160 --> 00:28:45,600
myself, with Shaochuan and Rutang,

527
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:47,520
